      "rationale": "Three mesh refinement levels were evaluated. Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness changed by <1% between the medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirmed grid convergence index <1.5%. Final mesh comprises approximately 420,000 second-order tetrahedral elements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals and energy balance satisfy manufacturer-recommended convergence tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals converged to <1e-5 relative tolerance for all load steps. Energy balance error <0.1%. Default Ansys sparse direct solver used with double precision arithmetic."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented review process and independent verification of model setup reduce probability of analyst error.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second analyst. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were verified against the ASTM F1717 test configuration drawings. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
