      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form is justified relative to the physics of the COU; simplifying assumptions are documented and their impact assessed.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium with bilinear kinematic hardening was selected based on published Ti-6Al-4V ELI stress-strain data. UHMWPE block modeled as linear elastic; sensitivity analysis showed <3% impact on construct stiffness. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) applied at screw-block interface based on literature values. Model form assessed as adequate for quasi-static compression-bending."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
