    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment result is Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs required level 3) is acknowledged and accepted given the quasi-static nature of the COU and the conservative bounding character of the single test condition. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for predicting compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the defined context of use.",
